SparseBrainVector         package:NeuroImage         R Documentation

_a _f_u_n_c_t_i_o_n _t_o _c_r_e_a_t_e _a _n_e_w _S_p_a_r_s_e_B_r_a_i_n_V_e_c_t_o_r _i_n_s_t_a_n_c_e

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     A convenience creation function for the SparseBrainVector class.  
     This function can construct a 4-dimensional sparse data structure
     from a matrix of values and a mask or 1d index vector.

_U_s_a_g_e:

             SparseBrainVector(dat, space, mask = NULL, indices = NULL)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

     dat: a 'matrix' of values where the number of rows or columns must
          equal the number of elements in the 'mask' or 'ndices'
          arguments.

   space: a 'BrainSpace' instance that encodes the 3d geometry of the
          to-be-created structure

    mask: an mask which must have the same dimensions as the 'space'
          argument.

 indices: an alternative to 'mask' (either one or the other must be
          supplied) which is simple a 1d vector of indices that map to
          the 3d coordinates. 

_V_a_l_u_e:

     an instance of the 'SparseBrainVector' class

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

     bbuchsbaum@rotman-baycrest.on.ca

